@prefix thesis: <http://github.com/seanchatmangpt/spec-kit-3t/thesis#> .
@prefix : <http://github.com/seanchatmangpt/spec-kit-3t/content#> .

#==============================================================================
# Minimal Thesis Example
# Demonstrates the minimum required RDF structure for thesis generation
#==============================================================================

# Thesis metadata
:minimal-thesis a thesis:PhDThesis ;
    thesis:hasTitle "A Minimal Thesis Example" ;
    thesis:hasSubtitle "Demonstrating RDF-First Thesis Generation" ;
    thesis:hasYear "2025" ;
    thesis:hasAbstract :minimal-abstract ;
    thesis:dedication "To students learning RDF-based documentation systems." ;
    thesis:acknowledgments "Thanks to the Semantic Web community for inspiration." ;
    thesis:keywords "RDF, Ontology, Thesis, Documentation" .

# Abstract content
:minimal-abstract thesis:hasContent """
This minimal thesis demonstrates the basic RDF structure required for generating
a complete PhD thesis using the Spec-Kit-3T framework. The constitutional equation
docs = μ(ontology.ttl) ensures deterministic generation from semantic knowledge.
""" .

# Author information
:author-example a thesis:Author ;
    thesis:hasName "Example Author" .

# Chapter 1: Introduction
:chapter-01 a thesis:Chapter ;
    thesis:chapterNumber 1 ;
    thesis:chapterTitle "Introduction" ;
    thesis:hasSection :ch1-sec1, :ch1-sec2, :ch1-sec3 .

:ch1-sec1 a thesis:Section ;
    thesis:sectionNumber 1 ;
    thesis:sectionTitle "Background" ;
    thesis:sectionContent """
This section provides background on RDF-based thesis generation.
The Spec-Kit-3T framework uses Turtle ontologies as the source of truth.
""" .

:ch1-sec2 a thesis:Section ;
    thesis:sectionNumber 2 ;
    thesis:sectionTitle "Motivation" ;
    thesis:sectionContent """
Traditional thesis writing suffers from format inconsistencies and manual duplication.
By treating documentation as a projection of knowledge graphs, we achieve guaranteed consistency.
""" .

:ch1-sec3 a thesis:Section ;
    thesis:sectionNumber 3 ;
    thesis:sectionTitle "Research Questions" ;
    thesis:sectionContent """
1. Can RDF ontologies serve as the single source of truth for academic writing?
2. Does the constitutional equation ensure deterministic generation?
3. What are the benefits compared to traditional LaTeX workflows?
""" .

# Chapter 2: Literature Review
:chapter-02 a thesis:Chapter ;
    thesis:chapterNumber 2 ;
    thesis:chapterTitle "Literature Review" ;
    thesis:hasSection :ch2-sec1, :ch2-sec2 .

:ch2-sec1 a thesis:Section ;
    thesis:sectionNumber 1 ;
    thesis:sectionTitle "Semantic Web Foundations" ;
    thesis:sectionContent """
The Semantic Web provides a framework for knowledge representation using RDF triples.
SPARQL queries enable structured extraction of information from these graphs.
""" .

:ch2-sec2 a thesis:Section ;
    thesis:sectionNumber 2 ;
    thesis:sectionTitle "Template-Based Generation" ;
    thesis:sectionContent """
Template engines like Tera and Jinja2 project structured data into various formats.
Combined with SHACL validation, this ensures data quality before generation.
""" .

# Chapter 3: Methodology
:chapter-03 a thesis:Chapter ;
    thesis:chapterNumber 3 ;
    thesis:chapterTitle "Methodology" ;
    thesis:hasSection :ch3-sec1, :ch3-sec2, :ch3-sec3 .

:ch3-sec1 a thesis:Section ;
    thesis:sectionNumber 1 ;
    thesis:sectionTitle "The 3T Methodology" ;
    thesis:sectionContent """
The 3T methodology combines:
1. TOML - Configuration management
2. Tera - Template rendering
3. Turtle - Knowledge representation
""" .

:ch3-sec2 a thesis:Section ;
    thesis:sectionNumber 2 ;
    thesis:sectionTitle "Pipeline Architecture" ;
    thesis:sectionContent """
The generation pipeline consists of five stages (μ₁-μ₅):
- μ₁: Load RDF and validate with SHACL
- μ₂: Extract data via SPARQL queries
- μ₃: Render templates
- μ₄: Write output files
- μ₅: Generate cryptographic receipts
""" .

:ch3-sec3 a thesis:Section ;
    thesis:sectionNumber 3 ;
    thesis:sectionTitle "Validation Strategy" ;
    thesis:sectionContent """
SHACL shapes enforce constraints on the RDF data before generation.
This prevents malformed output and ensures template compatibility.
""" .
